definition (required): A synonym type for describing abbreviations or initalisms
example of use: CHEBI:26523 (reactive oxygen species) has an exact synonym (ROS), which is of type OMO:0003000 (abbreviation)

definition (required): A synonym type for describing ambiguous synonyms
A synonym type for describing dubious synonyms
A synonym type for describing layperson or colloquial synonyms
example of use: EFO:0006346 (severe cutaneous adverse reaction) has an exact synonym (scar), which is of the type OMO:0003003 (layperson synonym)

definition (required): A synonym type for describing pluralization synonyms
example of use: CHEBI:23367 (molecular entity) has an exact synonym (molecular entities), which is of the type OMO:0003004 (plural form)

definition (required): A synonym type for describing UK spelling variants
example of use: CHEBI:16189 (sulfate) has an exact synonym (sulphate), which is of the type OMO:0003005 (UK spelling synonym)
